===Etymology===
From Middle English < Old English [[sunne]] < Proto-Germanic '''*sunnon''' < Proto-Indo-European '''*s(u)wen-''', an alternate form of PIE base '''*saewel-''' (to shine). Cognates include German [[Sonne]], Latin [[Sol]], Russian [[Солнце]] (Solntse) and Greek [[ήλιος]] (hélios).

===Proper noun===
'''Sun''' or '''sun'''
# The star at the centre of our [[solar system]].

